[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating dynamic class loading**\n\nI’m grappling with a task that requires understanding open-ended dynamic class loading and error handling. The test mentions using dynamic loading by class name, which raises questions for me — is that truly dynamic if the class is included at build time? It seems native support for Class.forName is applicable only if configured correctly. Maybe I shouldn’t use that fallback line? I also notice there’s an uncovered line at 1102. I wonder if catching unsupported features would be a good idea, as it might prevent the rest from executing under native conditions.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02724edf013d5af80169f71b84ff8c81a2924ce1b03a514345\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9xuYHsVg5rEOjtM58063xS0lslnqpby-yqqAc3CxRHbYPPYbeBmqyyDx4C24KKZMBDr0oLgeUnkJByaXlK2L1GiZCNt9LgsrZx9Me_Wrvh-NiknmgSvnIa6qa_09oERCkqBX9ed-q9vkIFbDZ2b321-SsEa4mk8f-uOgfwVtPy1c29r74Avu_zG97t34F_jmIz6sb4-VL8D9gaeR4RreLxkewxc2SZNj3aWMQeauGOMi8Ipc6FFLWzB_1TkGIZiRlOVDhJAPKfQjzsHqRcikyj-pcAbByDGbelfs7Zv4wTEO4Q5nEuQ_5_b-5u2dNhLf4ks3J8ouYif3r4k_TkPCtU-UAL3CDVO3dcej5V8YV9G8hwh_UU2RUXTPbQlS1mI-UKxHGd54CFK_mz_tiv4QkHgKLvLDDgEAjfdDy_LXnhc8FynA09LltDyIxgo4iq6ktVFUwHUxRZT3UiNCktGjB4k7T2-yzdxHPWnzdOvhVuF8tzD5mSDvQAr8XnabM0uvuGaA-SlzlPNXFOZqd-8u-t3J8XYe1xEIlaYpJazehnFyXRbKtYlPEfqqzZY_TsezUQzIbeem4XRksVo1xtq1IACFNO33C_mIyzBnNivBkVM9XpnUYVS-QYHGvBQPt5sNMYGw1brZAufPkTU6tp2Qpqgk-Ii8HRnYZhkXZK2Oo76eNLyaHmH_V98tNsorOD3s6pDU5jz8cuIqepmT5IXeGimbjpSpiodkSxyq5FstSxsBjzSUbdypAmQooRxS06G-fi1zSALuhZOqX1f8qrF0I7lkf1m98_YcqYcTkhLhuqfDzFmFjnm19kctOb6uHZgDh0BYFCkLSnpc0KZ9VtSU2m3jjNU2eRudmbDzsqo3Nni_0mlkewYSNZgZvvchY4qkCjL9n58LMNa8HoHQUmd1dDwkI8UekXr5qCgvIhzKuxuC7Is85aSX_iSLzg4P3Kth4cyJfX1CQR5IlqznoUvvvGNZb1EXgtZFARek-vUmwf9dV906LRU1uA7sB05rq-18FxccV3Ae3Jz57xeiX7wr0XYh5O3pE8ZIiPzBWzTpddrnNjwrzUBJlMqPD3MQLjqSx3MIKnl0K___Mg-lu96h2TyH48sUYpXrWlmTY6CFDri8WTduFcZ